{"type":"message","id":"35512417","parentId":"055a46af","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:35:18.430Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 20:35 GMT+2] OPERATION: ENDURANCE TEST & POST-MORTEM ANALYSIS.\n\n1.  **Test Prep (`tests/endurance_test.py`):**\n    *   *Load:* Generate 500 signals/min via `ProcessPoolExecutor` (simulating 4 workers).\n    *   *Features:* Utilize `AdaptiveRateLimiter` and `SharedMemory` manager.\n    *   *Duration:* Simulate 30 mins load (can be accelerated or run for 5 mins of intense burst).\n\n2.  **Execution (The Run):**\n    *   Set `DRY_RUN=True`.\n    *   *Monitor:* `psutil` loop checking RAM/CPU/Threads.\n    *   *Logging:* Stream to `logs/performance_audit.log`.\n\n3.  **Post-Mortem Analysis (Self-Improvement):**\n    *   *Jitter:* Parse log timestamps. Calculate StdDev of latency.\n    *   *Leak:* Check start_ram vs end_ram.\n    *   *Throughput:* Count signals processed vs generated.\n    *   *Fix:* If jitter > 10ms -> Adjust GC tuning or `sys.setswitchinterval`.\n\n4.  **DNA Sync:**\n    *   Update `docs/ACTIVE_CONTEXT.json` with performance metrics.\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Test Pass/Fail status.\n    *   Anomaly & Fix Report.\n    *   Shared Memory Stability.\n    *   RMT Readiness Verdict."}],"timestamp":1771180518428}}
